The President of the United States issued a statement respecting the decision made by the people of the United Kingdom in the UK Referendum. He emphasized the enduring special relationship between the US and the UK, as well as the importance of the UK's membership in NATO. The President also highlighted the significance of the relationship between the US and the European Union, acknowledging the EU's role in promoting stability, economic growth, and democratic values. The statement emphasized that the UK and the EU will remain important partners for the US, and that negotiations for their ongoing relationship will be crucial for ensuring stability, security, and prosperity for Europe, Great Britain, Northern Ireland, and the world.